2026-06-18 | Angle Between Hands of a Clock

	Question
Return the minimum angle between the hour and minute hands.
	Key Insight
The minute hand moves:
		360° in 60 minutes
So:
		minuteAngle =
		6 × minutes
The hour hand moves:
		360° in 12 hours
		30° per hour
But it also moves continuously as minutes pass:
		hourAngle =
		30 × hour
		+
		0.5 × minutes
If hour = 12:
		treat it as 0.
The required angle is:
		diff =
		abs(hourAngle - minuteAngle)
The smaller angle is:
		min(diff, 360 - diff)
	Approach
1.	Convert hour hand position to degrees.
2.	Convert minute hand position to degrees.
3.	Compute absolute difference.
4.	Return the smaller of:
		diff
		360 - diff
	Time Complexity
	O(1)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    double angleClock(int hour, int minutes) {
        hour %= 12;
        double hourAngle =
            30.0 * hour +
            0.5 * minutes;
        double minuteAngle =
            6.0 * minutes;
        double diff =
            abs(hourAngle - minuteAngle);
        return min(diff, 360.0 - diff);
    }
};
	Formula Used
	Key Insight
The minute hand moves 6° per minute, while the hour hand moves 30° per hour plus an additional 0.5° per minute. After computing both positions, the smaller angle is simply the minimum of the direct difference and its complement with respect to 360°.
